narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Music taught me the basics of part writing, and analysis of scores.
Ive donemusic but this class really helped me understand the philosophy behind it so much better
Had never studied music before and this was the perfect intro course for me. Engaging and interesting and you will learn a lot
This course improved my music proficiency level immensely! It has greatly increased my passion for music and taught me knew ways to appreciate sound.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I enjoyed learning all of the course material, but I do think that it went a bit too fast for a beginner.
Dr. Lalli is the BEST. He cares so much about music and his students

This course offers as many resources as you could want to help you learn music theory. The time the teacher invested in his students was incredible and the workload was unbelievably reasonable. It was a fantastic course!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. I think everyone should learn music at some point in their lives. I appreciated this course because it let me know that it is never too late to learn.
This is a great course, especially if you havent ever takentheory before
I would absolutely recommend this course to anyone interested in learning about music. Lalli was a fantastic teacher and was very available to help with questions, etc.
Anyone would enjoy taking this course, especially if you have played an instrument before but never really studied theory. This is one of the most enjoyable classes I've taken at Yale so far!
